# Dashboard UI Design Principles

Design conventions for RBIP dashboard panels: **flat surfaces**, **progressive disclosure**, and **clear hierarchy without nesting cards**.

## Core Philosophy

- **Flat hierarchy**: Prefer **one** outer frame (page → card/panel). Avoid **nested bordered cards** for every inner block; use spacing, `divide-y`, and type instead (aligns with `design-elements-commonality.mdc` — flat over “AI box stacks”).
- **Flat ≠ one visual plane**: You can still create **layers of meaning** with **numbering**, **typography**, and **grouping**—users scan steps and titles, not extra chrome.
- **Progressive disclosure**: Show summary first, reveal details on interaction.
- **Clear confirmation**: Destructive or impactful actions need explicit confirmation.
- **Visual clarity**: Spacing, dividers, and type over stacked borders.

---

## Layout & hierarchy

### Flat structure (avoid nested cards)

```tsx
// ❌ Nested Card (bad)
<Card>
  <Card>
    <CardHeader>Title</CardHeader>
    <CardContent>Content</CardContent>
  </Card>
</Card>

// ✅ Flat layout — stripes between sections (good)
<form className="divide-y divide-border">
  <section className="pb-6">{/* chapter 1 */}</section>
  <section className="py-6">{/* chapter 2 */}</section>
  <section className="py-6">{/* chapter 3 */}</section>
  <div className="flex gap-2 pt-6">{/* actions */}</div>
</form>
```

### Numbered chapters (multi-step forms)

Use when a panel is a **short procedure** (e.g. team PCA preferences: floor → preferred PCA → slots → gym).

| Layer | Role | Typical classes / pattern |
|-------|------|-----------------------------|
| **Step badge** | Order cue; warm, not a harsh square | `rounded-full h-7 w-7` disc, e.g. `border border-amber-200/90 bg-amber-50 text-amber-950 shadow-sm`, `text-[11px] font-semibold tabular-nums`. `aria-hidden` on the digit if the `h3` text repeats the step. |
| **Chapter title** | What this step is about | `h3` + `text-sm font-semibold text-foreground`, **sentence case** (e.g. “Preferred PCA”, “Slot rank”). Lay out as `flex items-center gap-2.5` with badge + title. |
| **Subhead** | Second move **inside** the same chapter | `text-xs font-medium text-foreground`, e.g. **Pick** / **Order** under one “Preferred PCA” chapter. Use `mt-8` (or similar) before the second sub-block—**no** new bordered card. |
| **Helper / policy** | Longer explanatory copy | `text-xs text-muted-foreground`; emphasize key phrases with `font-medium text-foreground` spans. |

**Grouping rule:** If two blocks share one user goal (choose people **then** order them), use **one** `<section>` and **subheads**, not two separate numbered steps.

### Legacy subsection label (dense panels)

For small labels inside tables or compact toolbars where numbered chapters are overkill:

- `text-xs font-semibold text-muted-foreground uppercase tracking-wide mb-3`

### Dividers

- **Prefer** `divide-y divide-border` on the **parent** + `pb-6` / `py-6` / `pt-6` on children over repeating many `<hr>` tags—same visual rhythm, less boilerplate.
- **Also valid:** `<hr className="border-border" />` for a one-off break.
- Use `divide-x` / internal `<hr>` for **lists** (e.g. regular vs buffer rows).

