## Quick reference

### Numbered form chapter (snippet)

```tsx
<h3 className="mb-3 flex items-center gap-2.5 text-sm font-semibold text-foreground">
  <span
    className="inline-flex h-7 w-7 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-amber-200/90 bg-amber-50 text-[11px] font-semibold tabular-nums text-amber-950 shadow-sm"
    aria-hidden
  >
    1
  </span>
  Floor PCA
</h3>
```

### Collapsible group header

```tsx
<div className="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3">
  <button onClick={toggle}>
    {isExpanded ? <ChevronDown /> : <ChevronRight />}
  </button>
  <span className="font-medium">GROUP NAME</span>
</div>
```

### Staff row with expand

```tsx
<div className="flex items-center justify-between py-2">
  <div className="flex items-center gap-2">
    <button onClick={toggleExpand}>
      {isExpanded ? <ChevronDown /> : <ChevronRight />}
    </button>
    <span className="font-medium">{name}</span>
    <span className="text-xs text-muted-foreground">({rank})</span>
  </div>
  {pendingDelete ? (
    <ConfirmDeleteButtons />
  ) : (
    <GhostIconButton icon={<Trash2 />} onClick={() => setPendingDelete(id)} />
  )}
</div>
```

### Anti-patterns to avoid

- Nested `Card` deeper than the outer panel without a strong reason.
- Multiple border layers for every inner block.
- Native `<select>` elements (use Radix Select — see `design-elements-commonality.mdc`).
- Emoji as icons.
- No confirmation for destructive actions.
- All content visible when progressive disclosure would reduce noise.
- **Numbering every unrelated widget** — reserve numbered chapters for real multi-step flows.
